annotationA: Molybdenum cofactor synthesis protein cinnamon; Catalyzes two steps in the biosynthesis of the molybdenum cofactor. In the first step, molybdopterin is adenylated. Subsequently, molybdate is inserted into adenylated molybdopterin and AMP is released; In the N-terminal section; belongs to the MoaB/Mog family
annotationB: Probable sulfite oxidase, mitochondrial; Molybdenum ion binding; heme binding; electron carrier activity; sulfite oxidase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: oxidation-reduction process; sulfur compound metabolic process; protein catabolic process
